you know, a certain ordinance. It's not good practice. So I hope that we can get legal reviews from KP Law when we request it. Obviously, as my colleagues have been saying, I think the official position is that KP Law represents the city. Realistically, you know, it's the mayor who sets contracts. It's the mayor who hires them. It's the mayor who can choose to switch law firms.

175
